race.comment: THREEFOLD (5) showed good early dash and raced on the speed at the first run back from a break last start before fading to finish just shy of the frame in sixth at Moruya. Had some excuses and is sure to have come on with that run under her belt. McDougall goes on from an ideal draw. Bold showing anticipated. SCREEN SPIRIT (6) was comfortably accounted for when fifth but his two runs prior to kick off his career were full of merit, most notably his maiden win two back. Has good early speed and can take advantage of the low draw. Definitely worth another chance. SHERIDAN STREET (2) is ready to make her return after enjoying a successful debut prep. Scored in her first start, so suspect she will be up for this. PERFECTLY GOOD (1) wasn't beaten far when first-up last campaign and can be in the finish despite a sticky barrier.
